  "prompt": "What is heterosexual?",
  "response": "\"Heterosexual\" is a term used to describe a sexual orientation in which a person is romantically and sexually attracted to individuals of the opposite gender. For example, a heterosexual man is typically attracted to women, and a heterosexual woman is typically attracted to men. Heterosexuality is one of several sexual orientations, others including homosexuality (attraction to the same gender), bisexuality (attraction to two or more genders), and asexuality (little or no sexual attraction to any gender). The term is often used in discussions about sexual identity, relationships, and society.",
